**Deploying fix — C1 TrustAlign Gate Enforcement**

Calling worker sub-agent to apply schema and logic changes...

```diff
// outbox_schema.json — BEFORE
{
  "draft_id": "string",
  "content": "string",
  "ready_to_publish": true   // ← ambiguous, caused the bug
}

// outbox_schema.json — AFTER
{
  "draft_id": "string",
  "content": "string",
  "review_status": "pending" | "in_review" | "approved" | "rejected",
  "trustalign_cleared": false,         // ← explicit boolean gate
  "trustalign_verdict_at": null,       // ← timestamp of clearance
  "publish_authorised": false          // ← only true when BOTH above are set
}
```

```diff
// engage-x publish_gate.js — BEFORE
if (draft.ready_to_publish) { publishNow(draft) }

// engage-x publish_gate.js — AFTER
if (
  draft.review_status === 'approved' &&
  draft.trustalign_cleared === true &&
  draft.publish_authorised === true
) {
  publishNow(draft)
} else {
  log.warn(`[engage-x] Publish blocked — TrustAlign not cleared. draft_id: ${draft.draft_id}`)
  notifyEcho('publish_gate_blocked', draft.draft_id)
}
```

**Additional safeguard added:**
- TrustAlign sub-agent now writes its verdict *directly* to `trustalign_cleared` field — engage-x cannot modify it
- Echo receives a `publish_gate_blocked` event if engage-x ever tries to publish without clearance
- Retroactive: all 3 queued drafts for next week have been re-validated through updated schema ✅

**Worker task logged:** `worker_task_20260220_1631` — changes applied to staging, pending push to prod.
